Four suspected robbers were arrested within 15 minutes of allegedly stealing money and a TV set from a house in KwaNobuhle, Uitenhage yesterday. Police spokeswoman Captain Gerda Swart said the robbers kicked open the front door of a house in Amanzi Crescent and threatened the homeowner with a gun, before fleeing in a VW Polo with a plasma TV and money. The homeowner notified the police. Four suspects were arrested after a car chase. All the stolen items from the house were found inside the car. The men, aged 26 to 38, will appear in the Uitenhage Magistrate s Court today. In Motherwell yesterday, a couple was held at gunpoint in their Mbiza Street home by two robbers. After first demanding money, the robbers fled with the couple s cellphones. This comes days after a Seaview man was stabbed in a robbery at his home. Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share